The VGA text memory is all spaces (0x20 with attribute 0x07) - the screen is blank. The boot process might be hanging on `net start` or `DOSIDLE.EXE`. Let me modify the AUTOEXEC.BAT to skip problematic commands.

{
  "analysis": "The text buffer shows all blank spaces - boot is likely hanging on one of the startup commands (net start, dosidle, or smartdrv). Need to modify the AUTOEXEC.BAT to simplify boot and ensure Windows starts properly.",
  "plan": "1. Unmount the image. 2. Create a modified AUTOEXEC.BAT that skips network and dosidle. 3. Write it to the image using mtools. 4. Restart QEMU.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ps aux | grep qemu | grep -v grep\n",
      "duration": 0.5
